SIMPLE: endowment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Endowment
<hw>En*dow"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of bestowing a dower, fund, or permanent provision for
support.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is bestowed or settled on a person or an
institution; property, fund, or revenue permanently appropriated to any
object; <as>as, the <ex>endowment</ex> of a church, a hospital, or a
college</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is given or bestowed upon the person or
mind; gift of nature; accomplishment; natural capacity; talents; --
usually in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His early <qex>endowments</qex> had fitted him for the work he was
to do.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endozoa</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
